igures including the Venetian nun and political theorist Archangela Tarabotti, the French feminist writer Hortense Allart, and others in a study that closely examines the material bases—manuscripts, letters, books, archives, and bodies—of writing as generators of social relations that organize and conserve knowledge in particular political arrangements. In her highly original study Jed reorganizes republicanism in history, providing a new theoretical framework for understanding the work of the scholar and the social structures of archives, libraries, and erudition in which she is inscribed.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aItalian literaturey16th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aPolitics and literaturezItalyxHistoryy16th century. 0aRepublicanism in literature. 0aRepublicanismxHistory. 0aRepublicanismzItalyzFlorencexHistoryy16th century. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / General.2bisacsh  aalessandro de medici.  achaste thinking.  aclassical scholar.  acultural studies scholars.  aearly modern cultural studies.  aeuropean archives.  aeuropean family history.  aeuropean history.  aeuropean libraries.  aeuropean literacy.  aeuropean literature.  aeuropean political history.  afamily and gender.  ahistory of republicanism.  aitalian history.  aitalian literary criticism.  aitalian scholars.  aliterature interpretation.  aliterature professors.  alorenzino de medici.  arepublican politics.  arepublican thought.  asocial structures.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052026769540uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095005440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520950054423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520950054/original  a978-3-11-069